---

<DocsLayout
  title="Getting started"
  description="Install ilyStream, walk through the first-launch checklist, and connect to OBS so you can go live in five minutes."
  slug="getting-started"
  updated="May 2026"
  readingTime="5 min"
  toc={toc}
>
  <p>
    This guide walks through installing ilyStream on a Windows PC, the first-launch
    checklist, and the minimum configuration to go live with OBS. Once you finish,
    you can drop into any of the integration guides to wire up lights, alerts,
    and the DeskThing companion.
  </p>

  <h2 id="install">Install ilyStream</h2>
  <p>
    ilyStream ships as a standard Windows application. Pick the installer if this
    is your stream PC and you want auto-updates, or the portable build if you are
    testing.
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Download the installer.</strong> Grab <code>ilyStream-Setup-0.0.8.exe</code> from the <a href={withBase('download/')}>Download page</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Run the installer.</strong> Double-click the file. If Windows SmartScreen warns about a new publisher, click <em>More info</em> &rarr; <em>Run anyway</em>.</li>
    <li><strong>Launch ilyStream.</strong> Open it from the Start menu or the desktop shortcut the installer created.</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="callout">
    <span class="callout__icon">i</span>
    <p><strong>Portable build.</strong> Prefer no install? Download <code>ilyStream-Portable-0.0.8.exe</code>, drop it in a folder, and run it. It stores config beside the executable.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="first-launch">First launch</h2>
  <p>
    On first launch ilyStream opens to the Studio workspace with a default scene.
    Take a minute to walk the three workspaces you will use the most:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Studio</strong> &mdash; scene canvas, source list, preview, and audio mixer.</li>
    <li><strong>Alerts</strong> &mdash; event rules, sound and image asset libraries.</li>
    <li><strong>Settings</strong> &mdash; OBS connection, encoder, integrations, personalization.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Pick an encoder</h3>
  <p>
    Open <strong>Settings &rarr; Broadcast</strong> and choose the hardware encoder for your GPU:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>NVENC</strong> for NVIDIA cards.</li>
    <li><strong>AMF</strong> for AMD cards.</li>
    <li><strong>QuickSync</strong> for Intel iGPU or Arc.</li>
    <li><strong>x264</strong> as a CPU fallback.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="connect-obs">Connect OBS</h2>
  <p>
    ilyStream pairs cleanly with OBS via the WebSocket plugin built in to OBS 28+.
    This lets ilyStream control scene transitions and lets you add ilyStream
    widgets to OBS as browser sources.
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Enable WebSocket in OBS.</strong> In OBS, open <em>Tools &rarr; WebSocket Server Settings</em>. Toggle <em>Enable WebSocket Server</em>, set a password, and copy the host, port, and password.</li>
    <li><strong>Add the connection in ilyStream.</strong> In ilyStream, open <em>Settings &rarr; OBS</em>. Paste the host, port, and password. Click <em>Connect</em>.</li>
    <li><strong>Verify scene names.</strong> Once connected, ilyStream lists your OBS scenes. Make sure the scene names match what your overlays and triggers expect.</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="callout callout--success">
    <span class="callout__icon">&check;</span>
    <p><strong>Connected.</strong> You now have a working studio. The next thing most creators set up is overlays in OBS &mdash; see the OBS browser sources guide.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="go-live">Go live</h2>
  <p>
    With OBS connected and scenes mapped, you can start the broadcast from OBS as
    usual. ilyStream rides along: alerts, TTS, and any wired integrations all run
    against the live session.
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Start streaming in OBS.</strong> Click <em>Start Streaming</em> in OBS.</li>
    <li><strong>Confirm audio routing.</strong> Watch the ilyStream mixer meters &mdash; TTS and soundboard hits should show up alongside your mic.</li>
    <li><strong>Test an alert.</strong> Open <em>Alerts</em> in ilyStream and use the test button to fire a sample event.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="next-steps">Next steps</h2>
  <p>Pick the integrations you actually need:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href={withBase('docs/obs/')}>OBS browser sources</a> &mdash; add ilyStream widgets and alerts to your scenes.</li>
    <li><a href={withBase('docs/audio-tts/')}>Audio routing &amp; TTS</a> &mdash; configure the broadcast mix and chat TTS voices.</li>
    <li><a href={withBase('docs/philips-hue/')}>Philips Hue</a> &mdash; pair the Bridge so chat events can flash your lights.</li>
    <li><a href={withBase('docs/govee/')}>Govee</a> &mdash; add Govee fixtures via the Developer API.</li>
    <li><a href={withBase('docs/deskthing/')}>DeskThing pairing</a> &mdash; turn a Car Thing into a hardware deck.</li>
  </ul>

